<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Tempest Warned of in Western France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 3 (Xinhua) -- France's National Center of
Highway Information CNIR Saturday warned that the people returning
home from New Year vacation should remain vigilant when driving
their cars, as a new tempest is expected to strike western France
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The CNIR asked traveller to reduce the speed of their vehicles
in the region struck by storms and reschedule their travel plans
if necessary.
</P>
<P>
The official weather forecast station Meteo France expected
wind of more than 150 kilometers per hour would blow through the
areas bordering the English Channel and Bretagne, while
northcentral regions, including Paris, are also expected to be
subjected to strong wind and rainfalls Sunday.
</P>
<P>
One man was killed and 500,000 were deprived of electricity in
Bretagne and Loire-Atlantique region when a strong tempest arrived
Thursday night and Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980104.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Parties in Ethiopia's Somali Region to Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Somali
Democratic League (ESDL) and the Ogaden National Liberation Front
(ONLF) have agreed to merge into one and establish a joint
regional government.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency today, in separate and
joint meetings they held in the last four days in Jijiga, central
committee members of the two political organizations agreed on
the merger and formed a joint committee for its success.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement reached by the two organizations, the
joint committee has 17 members of which nine are represented from
ESDL and the other eight from ONLF.
</P>
<P>
The joint committee has the responsibilities of leading work
of the regional government and merger activities until the merger
is fully realized.
</P>
<P>
The meeting has elected Abdulmejid Hussien as chairman of the
joint committee, Mohammed Mealin Ali, vice chairman and Mohammed
Drir, secretary.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the joint committee will
accordingly form the regional government in which the two parties
and other clans will have fair representation.
</P>
<P>
The regional government will have a 21-member executive
committee. Twelve of the seats will be held by ESDL, seven by
ONLF and the remaining two by clans yet unrepresented. 
</P>
</TEXT>
