<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Delivers 60,000-ton Fertilizers to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Some 60,000 tons of
fertilizers is being delivered to ethiopia's hinterland as part
of the effort to supply farmers in Oromiya and south Ethiopian
regions with farm inputs in the coming harvest seasons.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by the Agricultural Inputs Supply
Enterprise of Ethiopia in a statement today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said, the fertilizers being transported will be
distributed to farmers of the two stated regions during this
year's "small" and "big" rainy seasons.
</P>
<P>
It said about 34,800 tons of the total package has already
arrived in the enterprise's Nazret-Mojo central store, the
remaining amount needed for the big rainy season will be
delivered at 40 distribution stations.
</P>
<P>
There are two rainy or harvest seasons in Ethiopia. The small
rainy season from February to May produces about 10 percent of
the harvest of the year, while the big rainy season, which is
from June to September, will produce 90 percent of the
agricultural crops of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
