<HEADLINE> Chinese Army Donates Relief to Snowstorm-Hit Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Large quantities of relief
donated by the Central Military Commission and the Headquarters of
the People's Liberation Army (PLA) of China are being transported to
three snowstorm-hit prefectures in the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The prefectures are Nagqu and Ari in north Tibet and
Shigaze in the south.
</P>
<P>
Since mid-September last year, when Nagqu was severely attacked
by heavy snowstorms, the armed forces have made great efforts to
assist the calamity-hit areas.
</P>
<P>
The relief materials sent this time include 2,000
fur overcoats, 4,000 cotton-stuffed quilts, 6,000
cotton-stuffed coats, 80 tents and 20,000 pieces of candles.
