<HEADLINE> North China Province Use More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 4 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province used two billion US dollars in foreign funds during 1997,
up 24.9 percent on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Total investments included 1.5 billion US dollars in direct
foreign investment and loans of 500 million US dollars from
foreign sources.
</P>
<P>
Funds were invested in a number of projects, including a cement
works, an expressway linking Shijiazhuang, the capital of Hebei
Province, with neighboring Henan Province to the south, three
power plants and an environmental project north of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The province has used foreign capital totalling 6.5 billion US
dollars, including 4.5 billion US dollars in direct foreign
investment. 
</P>
