<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Plans Use of Overseas Funding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
plans to introduce 10 billion US dollars in overseas investments
during 1998.
</P>
<P>
The vast majority of overseas funds will be used for the
development of local hi-tech projects in the electronics,
machine-building, biochemical, pharmaceutical and
telecommunications sectors, as well as 30 leading enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, a major economic power, led the nation in 1997 by
consummating overseas investment contracts valued at some 8.36
billion US dollars, up 18 percent on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to increase its use of overseas funding and
issue an increased volume of bonds during 1998. Various profitable
local enterprises will gain exchange listings and large basic
construction projects will introduce the BOT (build, operate,
transfer) method. 
</P>
