<HEADLINE> Kuwait Bourse Witnesses Remarkable Hike Starting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Stock Exchange
Market witnessed a 45.5 points hike last week with the index
closing at 2651.8 points comparing with 2606.3 points in the
previous week, maintaining a bullish trend at the start of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait News Agency today quoted a weekly bourse report as
saying that the shares jumped by 77.8 percent, their value by 70.5
percent and the number of monetary transactions by 10.8 percent
compared to those the week before.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, during the week ending Saturday, up to
359.3 million shares changed hands with a value of 142.2 million
Kuwaiti dinars (469.26 million U.S. dollars) over 5,792 deals.
</P>
<P>
Up to 33.9 billion shares exchanged hands with a value of 10.4
billion Kuwaiti dinars (34.32 billion U.S. dollars) over 588,174
deals in 1997, registering an average surge of 32 percent for the
volume, 82 percent for the value and 90.75 percent for the
transactions, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The value of shares of 52 companies out of the 73 listed
companies registered a jump and only seven companies recorded a
drop during the past year, according to an annual report of the
stock exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
