<HEADLINE> More Handicapped People Imployed in Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Work units in southwest China's
Yunnan Province will employ handicapped workers at a ratio of 1.5
percent to the total work force in the province, as of January 1.
</P>
<P>
This is stipulated in a local code adopted by the Yunnan
Provincial Government.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has some 2.46 million disabled people, making up 6.16
percent of its total population. At present, only 23,000
handicapped people have jobs, or 0.74 percent of the number of the
province's total work force.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the Yunnan Provincial Federation
of the Disabled, it is an effective way to help the handicapped to
find jobs and ensure their rights to work.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that 26 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions in the country have passed similars local
laws.  
</P>
</TEXT>
