<HEADLINE> Second-Round Presidential Elections Start in Lithuania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania's presidential run-off
elections began Sunday at 7:00 a.m. local time (0500 GMT), the
Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
There are 2,039 balloting posts opening for 2,600,000 eligible
voters in the country.
</P>
<P>
Two of the seven presidential candidates entered the second
round of elections. They are Arturas Paulauskas, 44, former
procurator of the republic and 71-year-old ecologist Valdas
Adamkus.
</P>
<P>
During the first round of the elections held on December 21,
1997, none of the presidential candidates got a majority of the
votes. Paulauskas won 42.5 percent of votes while Adamkus got
28.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Paulauskas said Saturday that if he succeeds, he will appeal to
the United States for security guarantees and support for
Lithuania's admission to NATO.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope of expanding trade and economic
cooperation with Russia.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary results of this decisive round of elections are
expected to come out before midnight Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
