<HEADLINE> Levy-1stadd: Israeli Foreign Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Foreign Minister David
Levy announced Sunday in Tel Aviv his resignation from the
government, creating a crisis for government led by Benjamin
Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
Levy said in a press conference that he will send his
resignation letter to Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu after the
announcement.
</P>
<P>
He said that he resigned because Netanyahu's government has
abandoned the Middle East peace process and been ignoring the
difficulties of the poor of the country.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, Levy's resignation would come into effect 48
hours after his resignation letter to the prime minister. So the
prime minister still has two days to persuade him to change his
mind.
</P>
<P>
With the resignation of Levy from the government, Netanyahu
only enjoys a marginal majority of 61 seats in the 120-member
parliament. Levy's Gesher Party controls five seats in the
parliament in which Netanyahu has escaped narrowly several
no-confidance motions in the past several months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
