<HEADLINE> Dalian Garners Success in Use of Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The northeast China port city
of Dalian approved 1,200 foreign investment projects valued at 25
billion US dollars in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The city has drawn contracted foreign investments of 12.78
billion US dollars, with funds actually used standing at 5.35
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Huai Zhongyuan, deputy secretary of the Dalian Communist Party
Committee, said that overseas investment constitutes a major
pillar of the city's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Foreign companies account for one third of the city's total
fixed assets and contribute 17 percent to the annual industrial
output.
</P>
<P>
The city's tourism sector also recorded major achievements last
year by hosting 240,000 tourists from overseas and earning more
than 200 million US dollars, up 25 percent on 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
