<HEADLINE> Tourist Service Praised in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Tourists now enjoy not only the
beautiful landscape but quality service in Guilin, a picturesque
city in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The city's transport bureau has made great efforts to improve
the service of tourist vessels and taxies since early 1997. The
bureau launched service contests among the more than 100 tourist
boats under its jurisdiction in last April. Three ships were set
as pace-setters in the activity last year.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 10,000 survey sheets were distributed among the
tourists concerning service quality, tourist guides' work, prices
in catering service as well as management. Efforts were also made
to help training tourist guides.
</P>
<P>
Great progress was seen since the activity was launched. It is
a common practice that taxi drivers do not pocket the money they
pick up in Guilin, as elsewhere in the country. Incompleted
statistics showed that in 1997, taxi drivers turned over some
250,000 yuan the passengers left behind.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, tests were given to some 3,000 drivers concerning
traffic regulation, professional ethics, and traffic general
knowledge, in a bid to increase their competence as taxi drivers.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980104.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Announces Visa Policy for Central Asian States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has announced a
liberal and comprehensive visa policy to promote its relations
with Central Asian states in the fields of trade, tourism, culture
and education.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed here Sunday by Interior Minister Chaudhry
Shujaat Hussain while talking to the media, according to the
Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Under the policy, the issuance of visa has been made simple to
all bonafide businessmen and tourists of all Central Asian
republics, Hussain said.
</P>
<P>
The Interior Ministry of Pakistan has issued a notification of
the policy for the Central Asian states, he added.
</P>
<P>
Explaining main features of the visa policy, Hussain said that
40 U.S. dollars shall be charged for a six-month multiple entry
visa from a national of these states.
</P>
<P>
Tourists from these states will be allowed landing permit/visa
for 15-day on arrival through chartered flights arranged by
designated tour operators. Visa fee of 10 U.S. dollars will be
charged for single entry from each tourist.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Interior will issue the guidelines to all
concerned for implementation of the policy, Hussain said.
</P>
