<HEADLINE> HK Eligible voters Urged to Register Before Jan. 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 4 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Regional government Sunday urged
local citizens, who are eligible voters of functional
constituencies in the forthcoming legislative elections, to get
registered before the registration deadline set for January 16.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also urged corporate electors to appoint their
authorized representatives to cast their corporate votes during
the first general elections of the Legislative Council of the SAR
on May 24 and all the Election Committee subsector elections on
April 2.
</P>
<P>
The Election Committee will, in turn, elect 10 members to the
60-seat Legislative Council at the general elections on May 24.
</P>
<P>
One third of the legislators will be returned by five
geographical constituencies through proportional representation,
while 30 others will be selected by 30 business and professional
groups, known as functional constituencies.
</P>
<P>
Among 6.3 million Hong Kong citizens, a total of over 2.5
million people are eligible to take part in the forthcoming
elections.
</P>
<P>
In early December, a total of 30,000 voter registration
ambassadors knocked on every door all over the SAR to help
residents sign up as electors for the elections.
</P>
<P>
These voter registration ambassadors, who are teen-age
students, have visited nearly two million households during the
voter registration week from December 6 to 12.  
</P>
