<HEADLINE> World's Scientific Breakthroughs Highlighted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The world's top ten scientific
and technological breakthroughs in 1997 selected by Chinese senior
scientists were published today.
</P>
<P>
The leading scientific result, crowned by more than 500
academicians from the Chinese Academy of Sciences and the
Chinese Academy of Engineering, is that the British researchers
cloned a sheep from the DNA of a somatic cell of an adult sheep.
</P>
<P>
The second is that the American space ship, Pathfinder, made a
three-month exploration on the Mars and sent back large amounts of
pictures and data about the planet from 119 million miles away.
</P>
<P>
Other breakthroughs in astronomy include American astronomers
found direct evidences for the existence of black holes in the
universe, the United States launched the Saturn probe, "Cassini",
and the American astronauts successfully repaired the Hubble Space
Telescope.
</P>
<P>
The other major scientific events include American physicists
obtained atomic laser with sodium atoms, American scientists
worked out the structure of "X" chromosome with high accuracy and
produced artificial chromosomes, the prediction of world
scientists for "el nino" phenomenon have been proved, researchers
at an American laboratory announced that they observed a new
sub-atom particle, and British scientists found the structure of
hepatitis-B virus.
</P>
<P>
The selection of top ten scientific breakthroughs was
co-sponsored by the Chinese Academy of Sciences, the Chinese
Academy of Engineering and the Chinese Science News. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
