<HEADLINE> Beijing Boasts More Afforested Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The urban area of Beijing, the
Chinese capital, had had 16,500 hectares of afforested areas by
the end of 1997, 548 ha more than the figure a year ago.
</P>
<P>
To date, the green area in Beijing accounts for 32.23 percent
of its total area, or 7.18 square meters per person,
according to an official with the Beijing Municipal government.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1997 alone, the city planted 1.8
million trees and 1.3 million square meters of grass in urban
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"These green land not only makes the city more
attractive, but also helps improve the capital's ecological
environment," said the official.
</P>
<P>
Beijing plans to increase its green area coverage rate in urban
areas to 35 percent, or eight square meters per person, by the
end of the century, according to the official. 
</P>
