<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenyang Hospital Succeeds in Liver Transplanting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The No.1 Hospital of
Shenyang-Based China University of Medical Sciences has succeeded
in a liver-transplanting operation.
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old liver receiver, Zhao Changjiu, has recently
left the hospital after the operation which was conducted a month
ago.
</P>
<P>
The experts of the hospital said that Zhao's new liver is now
functioning well and Zhao is able to live like others.
</P>
<P>
On November 25 last year Zhao received the new liver to replace
his original one, for he had suffered cancer of common bile duct.
</P>
<P>
It took eight hours for the doctors to remove his disabled
liver and transplanted the new one. The biles came out 15 minutes
after all the ducts of the new liver were connected with the
original ducts.
</P>
<P>
On the fourth day after the operation, Zhao's liver resumed
normal operation and in the next few days, Zhao overcame
infections.
</P>
<P>
It is the second liver-transplanting case that the hospital has
done in the past three years. The hospital failed in its first
transplanting and the patient died 12 days after the operation due
to infections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
