<HEADLINE> 10,000 Dropouts in North China Province Resume Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000 primary and
middle school dropouts in Zuoquan County, north China's Shanxi
province, have resumed education.
</P>
<P>
The county, a revolutioary base during the Anti-Japanese War
(1937-1945), was hit by a serious flood last year, which destroyed
66 schools. After the flood, it began to build schools for the
dropouts.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, the county has invested 15 million yuan in the
construction of 102 primary and middle schools, with a floor space
of 30,000 square meters. 
</P>
