<HEADLINE> Certificates Issued to HK Public Notaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Justice
has issued in this southern Chinese city certificates to 41
Hong Kong public notaries as China-appointed attesting officers
in succession.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Minister of Justice Zhang Geng said the system to appoint
Hong Kong attesting officers has settled the question of using
legal documents in inland areas and Hong Kong, which are under
two different legal systems, thus safeguarding the legitimate
rights and interests of parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
He also said that his ministry will continue to implement and
improve the system to appoint attesting officers and increase the
number of the trustees.
</P>
<P>
Those applying for a new term upon the expiration of their
attesting terms will be examined and assessed in time, and those
proved to be qualified will be appointed in succession, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Since the system to appoint attesting officers in Hong Kong was
introduced by the Ministry of Justice in 1981, more than 200
attesting officers have handled some 400,000 cases involving Hong
Kong residents' legal cases in inland areas.  
</P>
