<HEADLINE> 850,000 Farmers In Shanxi Rise out of Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 850,000 farmers in
north China's Shanxi Province have risen out of poverty by
overcoming the effect of the drought hitting the province in 1997,
according to the People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has given priority to poverty relief
in recent years. More than 20,000 cadres have been sent to rural
areas across the province to help poor rural residents eliminate
poverty.
</P>
<P>
Comprehensive development projects for mountainous regions have
been launched, with tree planting and fruit cultivation becoming a
growth area for the local economy.
</P>
<P>
In the province's Luliang mountainous region, an old
poverty-stricken areas, 430,000 rural households in 113
townships have risen out of poverty by planting trees. 
</P>
