<HEADLINE> North China Province Cuts Textile Scale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 4 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province is cutting the scale of its textile industry, following
orders from the China National Textile Council.
</P>
<P>
The province's number of spindles has been reduced by 750,000
to three million in about seven years. Meanwhile, 110,000 textile
workers, about 30 percent of the province's textile workforce,
were laid off and entered the service industry sponsored by the
province's various textile companies.
</P>
<P>
The province's textile industry is also undergoing structural
overhauls, with many small companies merging into big group
companies, reducing some small brands. The province has 42 brands
of textile products recognized as famous national brands.
</P>
<P>
China plans to reduce about 10 million outdated and backward
spindles within three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
