<DOCNO> XIE19980104.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ellwood Hands Australia a Successful Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Australian teenager Annabel
Ellwood gave Australia a dream start in the 585,000 U.S. dollars
Hopman Cup, eclipsing Asa Carlsson of Sweden in straight sets in
Australian coastal city of Perth Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Buoyed by a capacity crowd of 8500, Ellwood overcame a nervous
beginning to triumph 6-4, 6-4 in 84 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Ranked 93 in the world, the 19-year-old girl was jittery early
in the first set, and despite having break point opportunities,
trailed 0-3.
</P>
<P>
She then settled and, aided by erratic Carlsson groundstrokes,
particularly from her forehand, rallied admirably to snatch the
first set in 43 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Carlsson's mistakes continued in the second as Ellwood, growing
in confidence, not only kept the ball in play but attacked the
lines regularly.
</P>
<P>
The victory was secured on the second match point when a
Carlsson backhand flew the baseline.
</P>
<P>
"My heart-rate was definitely up at the start," a delighted
Ellwood told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"It is definitely up there up ... because you are playing for
your country."
</P>
<P>
Ellwood surprised no-one when she conceded the boisterous
crowd support had been a contributing factor in her success.
</P>
<P>
"It's great to have that atmosphere in here and have them on
my side," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
