<HEADLINE> Nicholson Wins World Yachting Championship Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PERTH, Australia, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Australian crew Chris
Nicholson and Daniel Phillips, sailing Schneider, have won the
49er World Yachting Championship with two races remained after
today's race.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports, in the first of four races
scheduled for today, Nicholson and Phillips, from Newcastle, New
South Wales, chalked up a second place, then followed it with a
third, to clinch the title.
</P>
<P>
They didn't grab their victory until American brothers
Jonathan and Charlie McKee, who had been second on the leaderboard
over night, made a fatal mistake.
</P>
<P>
The Americans cruised home first in the second heat, but were
disqualified from the race for making a premature start.
</P>
<P>
However the McKees are still in the fight for second place,
with their main opponents Morgan Larson and Kevin Hall from San
Francisco, while Germany's Marcus Baur and Philip Barth, are
also in with a chance.
</P>
<P>
The day witnessed the leading position was frequently changed
hands with Nicholson and Phillips were always near the front of
the fleet.
</P>
<P>
Despite having victory in hands, Nicholson and Phillips
decided to complete the last two races of the series. 
</P>
