<HEADLINE> Herbal Medicine Manufacturer Passes Assessment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin No.6 Chinese Herbal
Medicine Plant has passed the quality management assessment of GMP
(good manufacture practice) formulated by the World Health
Organization.
</P>
<P>
This marks a step forward for modern manufacturing of
traditional Chinese medicines.
</P>
<P>
Since the GMP in 1992, the Chinese Ministry of Health has made
great efforts to apply it to the quality management of herbal
medicine manufacturers across the country.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin No.6 Chinese Herbal Medicine plant spent more than
80 million yuan (about nine million US dollar) on technological
upgrading in 1991, making quality inspection an inalienable
part of the whole production process. All of its products now meet
quality standards. 
