<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Communist Party Targets Speeding National Renovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnam's communist party aims
to speed up the country's renovation process in its latest
resolution published here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, adopted by the fourth plenum of the party's
central committee late last month, also stressed the tasks of
mobilizing internal strength, raising the effectiveness of
international cooperation and practising thrift to fulfil
socio-economic targets for the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
It reviewed the achievement in implementing socio-economic
development tasks set forth by the 8th party congress and pointed
out the shortcomings of the economy in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
"These problems affected the economic environment, reducing the
growth rate and hiding potential threats to socio-economic
stability," the resolution said.
</P>
<P>
As one of the party's major policies, it was necessary to speed
up the economic restructuring and adjustment of the investment
structure, to go on renewing the country's financial-monetary
system, and to enhance the development and management of all kinds
of businesses.
</P>
<P>
The resolution pointed out that socio-economic renewal must be
closely linked with reform of the state apparatus and
administrative system.
</P>
<P>
It also mentioned the need to create more job opportunities,
eradicating hunger and reducing poverty.
</P>
<P>
The spirit of self-sovereignty and self-determination must be
heightened and traditional identities preserved while integrating
the country's economy into the region and the world, said the
resolution.
</P>
<P>
It also mapped out measures to enhance the the party's
leadership in state management, and to bring into full play the
people's role as masters in the country's economic and social
life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
