<HEADLINE> More Cholera Cases Found in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from a cholera
epidemic in Sri Lanka has risen to 12 as more confirmed cases were
reported last week, bringing the total number to 437, the Island
newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The cholera epidemic was first reported on September 29 last
year in Chilaw district in the northwestern coast, 75 kilometers
from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The number of cholera cases has been rising since the first
case was reported, although the Health Ministry has taken various
measures to try to bring the epidemic under control, the newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
Continuous heavy rains and the stagnation of rain water in
drains are considered to be the main cause for the spread of the
disease.  
</P>
