<HEADLINE> Baoshan Cold-Rolling Equipment Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The 1,420-mm plate steel cold
rolling system, listed as an important project for the third-phase
construction of the Baoshan Iron and Steel Group, were put into
production on a trial basis recently.
</P>
<P>
Information from the company said that this cold-rolling
system, consisting of five separate production lines, is most
advanced.
</P>
<P>
The system has a designed capacity of producing 700,000 tons of
electro-coated sheetings with specifications ranging from 0.18 mm
to 0.55 mm. The products will mainly be used for making of
autobiles and production of pop-top cans in food processing
industry.
</P>
<P>
The entire cold-rolling project, with a localization rate of 67
percent, cost 3.2 billion yuan. The overall design of the project
was undertaken by the Wuhan Iron and Steel Design Institute of
central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The project was built by the No.20 Metallurgical Construction
Company of the Baoshan Iron and Steel Group. Construction took
three years to finish, information from the group said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
