<HEADLINE> Itaipu Hydroelectric Plant Sets Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Itaipu, the largest
hydroelectric station in the world, generated a record 89.2
billion kilowatt-hours (KWH) last year for Brazilian consumers.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian general director of the Brazil-Paraguay
binational central said the output was 8.8 percent up over that of
1996.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-five percent of all electricity consumed in Brazil is
produced by Itaipu.
</P>
<P>
Two more 700,000 kw generating units would be installed in
Itaipu to increase its capacity, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The plant now has an installed capacity of 12 million
kilowatts, with 18 generating units of 700,000 kw each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
