<HEADLINE> Juvenile Delinquents Start New Lif (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Su, a young man in the south
China city who has broken the law, was very excited when he
learned that he can still continue his studies in school.
</P>
<P>
Su was sentenced to a two-year term of imprisonment, with a
suspension period of three years, for theft and robbery.
</P>
<P>
He was expelled from school.
</P>
<P>
Judges from the local court and specially-appointed jurors gave
him a helping hand and found a school where Su can go on with his
study.
</P>
<P>
Su was touched by the warm hearts of judges and jurors. He made
up his mind to behave himself and studied hard when he returned to
school.
</P>
<P>
A year later, the court decided to cut one year of the sentence
according in view of his good behavior in scho persisted and
finally entered college.
</P>
<P>
Su is just one of the five juvenile delinquents in Guangzhou
city who entered college with the help of a special project, which
has been in operation for three years, aiming to educate and save
juvenile delinquents.
</P>
<P>
During the past three years, the project helped more than 300
juvenile delinquents.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
