<HEADLINE> Juvenile Delinquents Start New Life (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In tandem with the implementation of China's policies of reform
and opening to the outside world, Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, has witnessed rapid economic
development and marked improvements in the lives of local
residents.
</P>
<P>
However, the city is also encounted with increasing cases of
crimes committed by younsters due to various reasons.
</P>
<P>
To educate these teen-agers, Guangzhou City's Intermediate
People's Court and the Guangzhou City Committee of the Chinese
Communist Youth League first put a project in operation which
involves specially-invited jurors in trying juvenile delinquents
in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Specially-invited jurors include outstanding Youth League
organizers and teachers, who are asked to conduct persuasion in
court and supevise education in school.
</P>
<P>
During the trial operation of the project between 1992 and
1993, 25 cases involving younsters were dealt with, 47 teen-agers
were sentenced, 30 of them with suspended sentences.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the efforts of judges and specially-invited jurors,
none of these younsters committed crimes again.
</P>
<P>
There are now over 300 specially-invited jurors serving the
city's childrens' court since the project was put into official
operation across the city in 1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980104.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Juvenile Delinquents Start New Life (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1995, the city set up a juvenile delinquents education
center to help those serving sentences.
</P>
<P>
Over 40 persons, including judges, specially-invited jurors,
and people who are concerned with the education of juvenile
delinquents, regularly visit the center to provide legal
assistance and psychological consultation, correct bad behaviors
of juvenile delinquents, provide guidance for their action and
help them make up their mind to contribute to society again.
</P>
<P>
These people are also responsible for introducing new social
developments to juvenile delinquents and help them find jobs or go
back to school after completing their terms in the center.
</P>
<P>
"Guangzhou City Youth Hotline" was opened in 1995 to provide
consultation on protecting the legitimate rights and interest of
juveniles, explain punishment on youngsters who have violated the
law, and spread legal knowledge and guide youngsters in studying
and making friends.
</P>
<P>
In August last year, the Guangzhou Juveniles Legal Assistance
Station and Legal Assistance Fund were established to provide free
legal consultancy and assistance for local and non-Guangzhou
youngsters.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the ratio of juvenile delinquents in the city
drops by an average three percentage points annually.
</P>
<P>
Activities mobilizing more work units and departments to join
the efforts to educate juvenile criminals have been started.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, Youth League committees from nine enterprises have
established links with local juvenile delinquents education
stations to undertake regular education services for youngsters.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
