<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Olympic Speedskating Team Formed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Olympic speed
skating lineup for the 1,500 meters event in Nagano was set
on Saturday after the qualifying competition.
</P>
<P>
Moira D'Andrea, who will compete in the 500 and 1,000 meters,
was second fastest Saturday but clinched the fourth and final
women's 1,500 meters spot based on last week's time.
</P>
<P>
Kirsten Holum clocked Saturday's fastest women's time with two
minutes 5.03 seconds, which was far behind D'Andrea's 2:03.96 set
on December 27.
</P>
<P>
The other women's qualifiers at 1,500 were Chris Witty, Becky
Sundstrom and Jennifer Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
Casey Fitzrandolph secured the final men's spot when Saturday's
best time of 1:54.93 by Timothy Hoffman failed to better
Fitzrandolph's 1:54.70 last week.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. men's 1,500m will also include KC Boutiette, who
pre-qualified based on World Cup results, Cory Carpenter and Dave
Tamburrino.  
</P>
</TEXT>
