<HEADLINE> South Korea's Kim Takes Women's 1,500 Speedskating Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Kim Moon-jung of South Korea
beat teammate Joo Min-jin to win the 1,500-meter women's title at
the World Junior Short Track Speedskating Championships in
St. Louis on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kim's winning time was two minutes and 30.239 seconds in the
first of four championship races while Joo finished in 2:30.352.
</P>
<P>
Joo, however, won the 500-meter race in 47.234, ahead of
Bulgaria's Kristina Vuteva in 47.975. Kim took the third with a
time of 74.993.
</P>
<P>
Canada's Andrew Lahey clinched the men's 1,500 title in
2:33.078. Yosuke Eguchi of Japan was second, followed by Cees
Juffermans of the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Canada's Francois-Louis Tremblay won the men's 500-meter with a
time of 45.151.
</P>
<P>
The match, which will conclude Sunday at the U.S. Ice Sports
Complex, is the final international competition before next
month's Winter Olympics in Nagano, Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
