<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Thai Committee to Deal With Illegal Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government has set up a
new committee to handle the problem of foreign illegal workers in
the country, according to a local press report Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The committee, made up of representatives of the National
Security Council, the three armed forces and the Police
Department, will draw up measures to deal with such workers, whose
number exceeds one million.
</P>
<P>
Only 300,000 have registered for a temporary work permit. When
the registration period expires in June, none of the registered
workers will have their permits extended.
</P>
<P>
The committee will look into international laws regarding war
refugees and decide how to repatriate them, Labor and Social
Welfare Minister Trairong Suwannakhiri said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
