<HEADLINE> Prodi to Visit India and Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Italian Premier Romano Prodi will
begin a week of visits to India and Bangladesh Monday, wrapping up
the 1997 Italian foreign policy initiative entitled the Asian Year.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in India, Prodi is expected to sign agreements
on fighting drug-trafficking, organized crime and terrorism, and a
declaration on the role of small and medium-sized industries in
the development of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In Bangladesh, with a population of 143 million and per capita
income at 270 dollars, Dacca authorities are expected to ask Prodi
A D to take account of the country's poverty and social and
political fragility in relation to Bangladeshi exports to Europe.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Prodi visited China, Indonesia, Japan, South
Korea and Singapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
