<HEADLINE> 20 Injured in Head-On Train Collision in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 3 (Xinhua) -- A head-on collision of two
trains an a station near this capital city injured at least 20
people Saturday, two of them seriously.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 4:45 a.m., when a train lost control
and collided with another train at the station.
</P>
<P>
The collision caused a fire in the first carriage of one of the
trains, trapping a passenger and a federal policeman who was
standing guard at the railroad line.
</P>
<P>
The fire was put out in three hours, and the two men were
rescued. 
</P>
