<HEADLINE> SFOR Soldier Killed in Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 3 (Xinhua) -- A Spanish soldier of NATO's
Stabilization Force (SFOR) in Bosnia was killed in a road accident
while on patrol Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav news agency Tanjug quoted a SFOR spokesman as
saying the soldier was killed when his armored vehicle slid off a
road. Two other Spanish soldiers were seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-one soldiers have lost their lives since the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization's SFOR was stationed in war-torn
Bosnia in December, 1995. Most of them died in road accidents and
by stepping on mines. 
</P>
