<HEADLINE> Anand Beats Karpov in World Chess Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Super grandmaster Viswanathan
Anand of India upset reigning FIDE champion Anatoly Karpov of
Russia in the second game of the six-game world chess championship
match in Lausanne, Switzerland, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Anand started a Spanish opening with white,
ensured his victory on the 42 move when Karpov had to resign on
the spot.
</P>
<P>
Karpov, 46, won the first game. 
