set 29 world records in 1997.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China will accelerate the introduction of a social security
system in 1998. Priority will be given to the establishment of a
unified social welfare administrative body, expansion of the
coverage of insurance for employment and promotion of the welfare
system for ensuring minimum living standards.
</P>
<P>
-- Despite difficulties that the country's textile industry as
a whole has encountered, textile mills in Shanghai, China's
leading manufacturing center, earned profits totaling 300 million
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
 "China daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China is expected to consolidate its position as the largest
recipient of overseas funds among developing countries with a
record capital inflow of 62 billion US dollars in 1997. This
represents a rise of more than 10 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
-- The state taxation authorities will step up efforts to
intensify tax collection from the non-State sector this year to
boost the nation's coffer.
</P>
<P>
-- Shanghai will ease its chronic traffic congestion by
introducing a system of 11 subway and 10 light rail lines,
according to a city government plan.
</P>
<P>
-- An anticipated increase in imports of high-tech and high
value-added equipment is expected to hurt China's machinery
industry, which plans to start massive restructuring this
year. 
