<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brown Retains Title in Durham Cross-Country Challenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 3 (Xinhua) -- John Brown of Britain took the
Durham Cross-Country Challange title in Durham, England, for the
second consecutive year on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Brown, third in last year's series, led the way from the early
stage of the course to finish in 31 minutes and 32 seconds, 22
seconds ahead of Yann Millon of France.
</P>
<P>
The Englishman became the first to win the men's race twice in
its 10-year history.
</P>
<P>
Tom Nyariki of Kenya was clocked in 32:13 for third in the
men's 9.3 km race.
</P>
<P>
Now Nyariki stands the top of the World Cross Challenge
standings after two events following his second place in Brussels
in the opening race last month.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 5.2 km event, Catherina McKiernan of Ireland
continued her dominance as she finished first easily in 20:04.
</P>
<P>
Liz Wilson of the United States was second in 20:22, followed
by Mariana Chirila of Romania in 20:36.
</P>
<P>
The 10th Durham International Cross Country was second round of
the 1997-98 International Amateur Athletic Federation's World
Cross Challenge series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
