<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 24,647 Assassinations in Colombia in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- 24,647 assassinations
were committed in Colombia last year, a figure of some 2,000 less
than that of 26,642 in 1996, says Saturday a report from the
Judicial Police Direction.
</P>
<P>
It can be gleaned from the figure of common homicides in 1997s,
that 68 persons died every day for these causes in Colombia,
almost three every hour.
</P>
<P>
The most violent department was Antioquia, where -- including
Medellin and Uraba -- 6,997 persons were assassinated.
</P>
<P>
The statistics of common homicides in the three main capitals
of the country is as follows: Medellin with 4,472 cases, Santafe
de Bogota with 2,702, and Cali with 1,753. The month in which more
assassinations were registered was May, with 2,192.
</P>
<P>
During 1997 6,175 persons in died of traffic accidents in
Colombia and 1,537 terrorist actions were perpetrated, says the
Colombian police report.
</P>
<P>
Last year 1,817 persons were kidnapped and 676 bank holdups
registered. Also 71,000 robberies were commited and 2,842 cases of
piracy on land registered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
