<HEADLINE> At Least 20 People Killed in Pakistan Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 4 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 people were killed
and several others injured on Saturday evening in a fatal road
accident near Jehlum, about 100 kilometers southeast of the
capital Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when an oil tanker coming from the
opposite side struck a truck which further collided with a
passenger bus and a car and caught fire, police said.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports by police said at least 20 people died on the
spot while several others were injured in the fire.
</P>
<P>
According to police and the Jehlum District administration,
traffic was suspended for about four hours.
</P>
<P>
Over-speeding has been blamed for the accident.
</P>
<P>
President Rafiq Tarar and Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif have
expressed deep grief and sorrow over the loss of lives in the road
accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
