<HEADLINE> Arafat to Meet Clinton in Washington Late January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) President Yasser Arafat will travel to Washington on January
22 and hold talks with U.S. President Bill Clinton on the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian news service, the Jerusalem Media and
Communication Center (JMCC), reported the PNA decision Saturday
evening.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, U.S. Middle East peace envoy Dennis
Ross will travel to the region to meet Arafat in the West Bank
city Bethlehem next Thursday as planned, JMCC said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has reportedly asked
Ross to postpone his Middle East trip until after he resolves the
budget crisis his government is now facing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli Prime Minister's Office announced Netanyahu
will visit Washington on January 20 and hold talks with Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Ross's mission here is to prepare for Clinton's separate
meetings with Netanyahu and Arafat in Washington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
